TY  - JOUR
T1  - An Algorithm for the Chebyshev Problem—With an Application to Concave Programming
AU  - Zangwill, Willard I.
Y1  - 1967/09/01
PY  - 1967
DA  - 1967/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.14.1.58
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.14.1.58
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 58
EP  - 78
VL  - 14
IS  - 1
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - The Chebyshev problem is to determine a point xα which solves maxα min i = 1,?, N{gi(x)}. By exploiting generalized inverses an algorithm is developed for determining xα. It is also shown that in a certain sense the Chebyshev problem is equivalent to the concave programming problem. Moreover, for the programming problem generated by the Chebyshev problem, the Kuhn-Tucker conditions are proven to be sufficient even though the feasible region may not be convex.
AB  - The Chebyshev problem is to determine a point xα which solves maxα min i = 1,?, N{gi(x)}. By exploiting generalized inverses an algorithm is developed for determining xα. It is also shown that in a certain sense the Chebyshev problem is equivalent to the concave programming problem. Moreover, for the programming problem generated by the Chebyshev problem, the Kuhn-Tucker conditions are proven to be sufficient even though the feasible region may not be convex.
